    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d10fn1">Sent to Washington by the United States Military
                        Attaché, London, via Army channels; forwarded by the White House Map Room to
                        Roosevelt, who was then at Charlottesville, Virginia, in telegram No. <gloss
                            target="#t_Red1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Red</hi>
                        </gloss> 51. For the full text of this message, see Churchill, <hi
                            rend="italic">Closing the Ring</hi>, p. 626.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-04">4 June
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President Roosevelt personal and top secret number 692.</p>
                <p>10. … I am deeply grieved that you cannot come before that very distant
                        date.<note n="2" xml:id="d10fn2">In a letter to Churchill dated May 20, 1944
                        (not printed), to which this telegram was a reply, Roosevelt had said: “I do
                        not believe I can get away for over a month.” (Roosevelt Papers)</note> Let
                    me know if I can help matters by a journey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <gloss target="#t_Prime1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
